[{"id":"VR596393","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR596391.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following approaches to treatment is used in this study?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR596393_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a bar graph. The vertical axis is labeled “Anxiety Rating,” and the numbers 0 through 10, in increments of 1, are indicated. The horizontal axis is labeled “Exposure to Spiders, in minutes,” and the numbers 0 through 10, in increments of 2, are indicated. Each of the numbers on the axis from 2 through 10 have one bar. The data represented by the bars are as follows. Exposure, 2 minutes; Anxiety rating, 9. Exposure, 4 minutes; Anxiety rating, 8. Exposure, 6 minutes; Anxiety rating, 7. Exposure, 8 minutes; Anxiety rating, 7. Exposure, 10 minutes; Anxiety rating, 3.\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR596391.g05.svg\" width=\"350\"/></div><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><p class=\"passage_para\">While working with individuals who have a spider phobia, Dr. Nielsen wants to determine whether exposing them to spiders will reduce their fears. Dr. Nielsen asks one participant to watch a ten-minute video about spiders and report the anxiety they experienced on a ten-point scale (1 equals \"not at all anxious,\" and 10 equals “extremely anxious”) every two minutes. The data Dr. Nielsen obtained from the participant are presented in the graph.</p></div></div></div>"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Behavioral</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Humanistic</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Cognitive</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Psychodynamic</p>"],"answer":0}]